#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn51.31"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn51.31:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 51 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 51 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.31:0.2"
msgid "3. Ayoguḷavagga "
msgstr "3. The Iron Ball "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 31. Moggallānasutta → moggalāno (pts1)
msgctxt "sn51.31:0.3"
msgid "31. Moggallānasutta "
msgstr "31. About Moggallāna "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn51.31:1.1"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "sn51.31:1.2"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "“What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn51.31:1.3"
msgid "katamesaṃ dhammānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā moggallāno bhikkhu evaṃmahiddhiko evaṃmahānubhāvo”ti? "
msgstr "What things has the mendicant Moggallāna developed and cultivated so as to have such power and might?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn51.31:2.1"
msgid "“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā bhagavaṃnettikā … pe … "
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. He is our guide and our refuge. …” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.31:2.2"
msgid "“catunnaṃ kho, bhikkhave, iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā moggallāno bhikkhu evaṃmahiddhiko evaṃmahānubhāvo. "
msgstr "“The mendicant Moggallāna has become so powerful and mighty by developing and cultivating the four bases of psychic power. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn51.31:3.1"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn51.31:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, moggallāno bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti—"
msgstr "Moggallāna develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm, and active effort. "

msgctxt "sn51.31:3.3"
msgid "iti me chando na ca atilīno bhavissati, na ca atippaggahito bhavissati, na ca ajjhattaṃ saṅkhitto bhavissati, na ca bahiddhā vikkhitto bhavissati. "
msgstr "He thinks: ‘My enthusiasm won’t be too lax or too tense. And it’ll be neither constricted internally nor scattered externally.’ "

msgctxt "sn51.31:3.4"
msgid "Pacchāpuresaññī ca viharati—"
msgstr "And he meditates perceiving continuity: "

msgctxt "sn51.31:3.5"
msgid "yathā pure tathā pacchā, yathā pacchā tathā pure; "
msgstr "as before, so after; as after, so before; "

msgctxt "sn51.31:3.6"
msgid "yathā adho tathā uddhaṃ, yathā uddhaṃ tathā adho; "
msgstr "as below, so above; as above, so below; "

msgctxt "sn51.31:3.7"
msgid "yathā divā tathā rattiṃ, yathā rattiṃ tathā divā. "
msgstr "as by day, so by night; as by night, so by day. "

msgctxt "sn51.31:3.8"
msgid "Iti vivaṭena cetasā apariyonaddhena sappabhāsaṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "And so, with an open and unenveloped heart, he develops a mind that’s full of radiance. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.31:3.9"
msgid "Vīriyasamādhi … pe … "
msgstr "He develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to energy … "

msgctxt "sn51.31:3.10"
msgid "cittasamādhi … "
msgstr "mental development … "

msgctxt "sn51.31:3.11"
msgid "vīmaṃsāsamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti—"
msgstr "inquiry, and active effort. "

msgctxt "sn51.31:3.12"
msgid "iti me vīmaṃsā na ca atilīnā bhavissati, na ca atippaggahitā bhavissati, na ca ajjhattaṃ saṅkhittā bhavissati, na ca bahiddhā vikkhittā bhavissati … pe … "
msgstr "He thinks: ‘My inquiry won’t be too lax or too tense. And it’ll be neither constricted internally nor scattered externally.’ … "

msgctxt "sn51.31:3.13"
msgid "iti vivaṭena cetasā apariyonaddhena sappabhāsaṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "And so, with an open and unenveloped heart, he develops a mind that’s full of radiance. "

msgctxt "sn51.31:3.14"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā moggallāno bhikkhu evaṃmahiddhiko evaṃmahānubhāvo. "
msgstr "The mendicant Moggallāna has become so powerful and mighty by developing and cultivating these four bases of psychic power. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.289, sc4
msgctxt "sn51.31:4.1"
msgid "Imesañca pana, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā moggallāno bhikkhu evaṃ anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti—ekopi hutvā bahudhā hoti, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hoti … pe … yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti. "
msgstr "And by developing and cultivating these four bases of psychic power, the mendicant Moggallāna wields the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying himself and becoming one again … controlling the body as far as the Brahmā realm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.31:4.2"
msgid "Imesañca pana, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā moggallāno bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī”ti. "
msgstr "And by developing and cultivating these four bases of psychic power, the mendicant Moggallāna realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And he lives having realized it with his own insight due to the ending of defilements.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn51.31:4.3"
msgid "Ekādasamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

